The paper deals with stochastic processes and their spectral properties, which are topics commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of a Markov chain and mixing conditions also suggests a connection to dynamical systems (cs.DS). The paper also mentions mean field games, which are often studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and the use of a second-order Taylor series approximation suggests a connection to mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
